paragraphs.text:
val PATH_TO_INPUT_DATA = "/Users/harihar/Downloads/train.csv"

case class Animal(
    id: String,
    name: String,
    year: Int,
    month: Int,
    day: Int,
    hour: Int,
    min: Int,
    sec: Int,
    outcomeType: String,
    outcomeSubtype: String,
    animalType: String,
    sexUponOutcome: String,
    ageInYears: Double,
    breed: String,
    breedSimple: String,
    color: String,
    timestamp: Long
)

def parseAgeIntoYears(ageStr: String): Double = {
    if (ageStr == "") {
        0
    } else {
        val split = ageStr.split(" ")
        val age = split(0).toInt
        val numPerYear = split(1) match {
            case "days" | "day" => 365
            case "month" | "months" => 12
            case "week" | "weeks" => 52
            case "years" | "year" => 1
            case _ => 1
        }
        age / 1.0 / numPerYear
    }
}

import spark.implicits._
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat

val formatter = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd")
val df = spark.read.csv(PATH_TO_INPUT_DATA)
    .map(row => {
        val date = formatter.parse(row.getString(2))
        Animal(
            row.getString(0),
            row.getString(1),
            date.getYear,
            date.getMonth,
            date.getDay,
            date.getHours,
            date.getMinutes,
            date.getSeconds,
            row.getString(3),
            row.getString(4),
            row.getString(5),
            if (row.getString(6) == "") "Unknown" else row.getString(6),
            parseAgeIntoYears(row.getString(7)),
            row.getString(8),
            row.getString(8) match {
                case "Domestic Shorthair Mix" => "Domestic Shorthair Mix"
                case "Pit Bull Mix" => "Pit Bull Mix"
                case "Chihuahua Shorthair Mix" => "Chihuahua Shorthair Mix"
                case _ => "other"
            },
            row.getString(9),
            date.getTime
        )
    })
df.toDF().registerTempTable("originalData")

* breed = Among the top three breeds, breed has a minor impact on outcome.

// Let's use cross validation to make this decision tree better.
import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.{CrossValidator, ParamGridBuilder}
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.MulticlassClassificationEvaluator

val dt = new DecisionTreeClassifier()
    .setLabelCol(FeatureVectorizer.indexed(labelCol))
    .setFeaturesCol(featuresCol)

val dtPipeline = new Pipeline()
    .setStages(Array(dt, labelConverter))
    
val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
    .addGrid(dt.maxDepth, Array(3, 5, 7))
    .addGrid(dt.impurity, Array("entropy", "gini"))
    .build()

val eval = new MulticlassClassificationEvaluator()
  .setLabelCol(FeatureVectorizer.indexed(labelCol))
  .setPredictionCol(predictionCol)
  .setMetricName("accuracy")
  
val cv = new CrossValidator()
  .setEstimator(dtPipeline)
  .setEvaluator(eval)
  .setEstimatorParamMaps(paramGrid)
  .setNumFolds(3)

val cvDtModel = cv.fit(train)
val cvDtPredictions = cvDtModel.transform(test)
cvDtPredictions.toDF().registerTempTable("cvDtPredictions")

// Let's examine the confusion matrix.
val metrics = MakeMulticlassMetrics(cvDtPredictions, FeatureVectorizer.indexed(labelCol), predictionCol)
metrics.confusionMatrix
metrics.accuracy
